        <h1><img src="<%=BreedIcon %>" alt="<%=SpeciesNamePlural %>" height="40" /> <%=SpeciesNamePlural %></h1>
        <img src="<%=image %>" class="main-article-image" alt="About Ostriches" width = 100%/>
        <div class="article-body clearfix">

            <p>The ostrich (Struthio camelus) is the largest bird in the world and are native to the savannas and deserts of Africa. They are flightless birds and are known for their long legs, powerful bodies, and distinctive appearance. Ostriches are raised for their meat, leather, feathers, and eggs.</p>
            
            <p>Ostriches are social animals that live in flocks, and they are well adapted to life in their arid habitats. They have a unique system of regulating their body temperature, and they also are able to store water in their bodies, which helps them survive in hot and dry conditions.</p>
            
            <p>Their diet primarily consists of plant matter, such as leaves, seeds, and fruit, as well as insects and small animals.</p>
            
            <p>In addition to their economic importance, ostriches also have cultural significance in many African cultures, where they are associated with strength, speed, and endurance.</p>

            <div class="article-float-right">
                <img src="OstrichesScotchEgg.jpg" alt="Ostrich Scotch Egg" />
            </div>

            <p>Ostrich eggs are large eggs that are laid by the ostrich, the largest bird in the world. They are the largest eggs of any species of bird, and can measure up to 15 cm (6 inches) in length and weigh up to 1.5 kg (3.3 lbs).</p>
            
            <p>Ostrich eggs have a unique and distinctive appearance, with a smooth, glossy shell that is typically cream or light brown in color. The shells are also very thick, which makes them difficult to crack, and they are often used for decorative purposes, such as in basket weaving and ornamental carvings.</p>
            
            <p>Ostrich eggs are also a source of food, and they are often used in a variety of culinary applications, such as boiled, fried, or baked. The egg white is high in protein and low in fat, while the yolk is rich and flavorful, and is used to add richness to dishes.</p>

            <p>In addition to their culinary and decorative uses, ostrich eggs also have a number of health benefits. They are a good source of nutrients, such as vitamin D, calcium, and iron, and they are also low in cholesterol and saturated fat.</p>

            <div class="article-float-left">
                <img src="OstrichesMeat.jpg" alt="Ostrich Meat" />
            </div>

            <p>Ostrich meat is a lean and healthy red meat. It is sold in specialty food markets and online. Ostrich meat has a rich, slightly sweet flavor and a tender, slightly gamey texture that is similar to beef. It is also a lean meat that is low in saturated fat and high in protein, making it a nutritious food choice.</p>
            
            <p>Ostrich meat can be prepared in a variety of ways, including grilling, roasting, and stir-frying, and it is often used as a substitute for beef in dishes such as burgers, stir-fries, and stews. It is also a popular ingredient in gourmet sausages and cured meats, such as salami and pepperoni.</p>

